Telecom Egypt (TE) announced the unification of the basic home landline packages into the WE landline package at EGP 20, which includes 120 local minutes and the service of showing the student number, starting from the January 2020 bill.

The company explained in a statement on Thursday that it was decided to cancel the previous EGP 15 package to start the packages from the basic package WE 20, and the company also provides its customers with other options of larger packages that suit the desires and needs of customers, namely the WE ground 35 package, and WE ground 65.

Telecom Egypt (ETEL) said it has not received any offers or correspondence to sell its stake in Vodafone, according to a newspaper.

The company said in a statement to the Egyptian Exchange (EGX) on Sunday that it has no intention of selling its stake in Vodafone Egypt during the current period.

Telecom Egypt said it is studying alternatives to deal with its investments in Vodafone Egypt.

The company said in a statement to the Egyptian Exchange on Wednesday that it is closely following Vodafone's intention to sell its stake in Vodafone Egypt to Saudi Telecom Company.

Telecom Egypt pointed out that the study of alternatives comes in light of its rights in accordance with the shareholders' agreement, and in light of the final form of the planned acquisition.

Telecom Egypt said in a statement to the EGX that it has approached the Egyptian Financial Supervisory Authority in accordance with the recommendation of its legal advisor to determine whether the potential transaction is subject to these provisions, which stated that the potential transaction is subject to purchase offers for the purpose of acquisition.

Telecom Egypt is currently considering alternatives around its 45 percent stake in Vodafone Egypt in light of the Saudi Telecom company's potential deal, the minister of communications and information technology said.

Telecom Egypt is a state-owned company and is not for sale, Talaat said, in a message of reassurance to the company's employees, according to the Middle East News Agency.

The minister explained that the only thing that is on offer is its stake in Vodafone Egypt.

Between the best and the best or the closest, there are several scenarios for Telecom Egypt to deal with its stake in Vodafone Egypt's capital as part of the potential deal for STC to acquire Vodafone Group's stake in its Egyptian unit.
Experts and analysts of the telecommunications sector in investment banks agreed that the scenarios include Telecom Egypt's tendency to abandon its non-governing stake in Vodafone Egypt, or the trend to activate the option and buy Vodafone's global share, while the third option is to maintain its stake and cooperate with the new potential partner.

Telecom Egypt has selected a consortium of EFG Hermes and Citibank to identify investment alternatives for the Vodafone Egypt deal, in which it owns about 45 percent, capital market sources said.

The Egyptian Competition Authority (ECA) announced today that it has received a request from Vodafone Egypt to study Telecom Egypt's use of the right of first refusal to purchase Vodafone's global stake in Vodafone Egypt with the Competition Protection Law No. 3 of 2005.

Telecom Egypt (ETEL) said it has studied its legal position on Vodafone's global sale of its stake in Egypt, which confirms that all its rights of pre-emption guaranteed in the shareholders' agreement and articles of association of Vodafone Egypt, or acceptance of a compulsory purchase offer, and any other rights guaranteed by laws. The company added in a statement to the Egyptian Exchange on Thursday that Vodafone Egypt has addressed the Competition Authority to inquire about the compatibility of Telecom Egypt's use of the right of pre-emption prescribed under the company's articles of association.

Telecom Egypt's (ETEL) board of directors has approved the appointment of Citibank and EFG Hermes as an investment bank to explore all available alternatives to deal with its investments in Vodafone Egypt.

The company added in a statement to the Egyptian Exchange on Thursday that the board of directors approved the authorization for the board of directors to donate for the fiscal year 2020, provided that it will be presented to the next ordinary general assembly.

Telecom Egypt (ETEL.CA) announced a net profit attributable to shareholders of EGP 4.399 billion in 2019, up 33% compared to EGP 3.2 billion in 2018.

Mubasher Tadawul's research attributed the increase in the company's profits in a research note issued today to a 21-fold increase in currency difference profits to reach EGP 1.57 billion in 2019 compared to EGP 76.7 million in 2018 as a result of the appreciation of the Egyptian pound against the dollar throughout the year.

Telecom Egypt said that the General Assembly, scheduled for March 23, 2020, will consider the dividend proposal for 2019.  The company said in a statement to the EGX on Sunday that the assembly will consider approving the board of directors' report on the company's activities during 2019 and the auditor's report for the past year.

Telecom Egypt (Telecom Egypt) has increased the capacity of landline internet packages offered to its customers, as part of the Ministry of Communications and Information Technology (MCIT) initiative to support students in the education process.

The ministry added in a statement issued on Tuesday that this coincides with the decision to suspend studies in schools and universities for two weeks as part of the precautionary measures taken by the state to confront the emerging Corona virus, thus making Telecom Egypt the first company in the telecommunications sector to implement the initiative.

Telecom Egypt (ETEL) announced the extension of the payment period for the January fixed phone bill, which was set for March 15, until the next bill due without disconnecting the service.

The company added in a statement issued today, Wednesday, this comes within the framework of the company's support for the state's efforts to confront the emerging Corona virus, and in solidarity with the precautionary measures to prevent the spread of the virus by reducing congestion and limiting exit unless absolutely necessary.

Mubasher Tadawul research reviewed the repercussions of the Coronavirus on the Egyptian Exchange and the preferred stocks to buy during the current time.

Mubasher Tadawul Research said in a report that the profitability multiple of the Egyptian stock market as a whole reached 6.37 times as of March 19, 2020, compared to the average CAPE ratio for the Egyptian Exchange of 13 times during the period from 2008 to the end of 2019.

She added that the rapid spread of the Corona virus forced most countries of the world, including Egypt, to take measures that can be described as protective measures in an unprecedented manner.

Telecom Egypt's General Assembly approved the distribution of a cash coupon to shareholders of 25 piasters per share for 2019.

The company said in a statement to the EGX that the assembly approved the distribution of EGP 426.76 mn to shareholders for last year, in addition to allocating about EGP 659.84 mn of last year's profits to employees.

Telecom Egypt announced the amendment of the working hours of the company's branches nationwide starting tomorrow, Wednesday, until the end of the ban period.

According to a statement issued by the company on Tuesday, it was decided to start work in the company's branches from half past eight in the morning until four in the afternoon.

The company stated that the new dates will be valid from Sunday to Thursday of each week, with Friday and Saturday being a weekly holiday.

Telecom Egypt announced that it will give its customers a one-month grace period to pay the annual subscription without applying any delay penalties.

Telecom Egypt confirmed in a statement issued on Wednesday that its decision comes within the framework of the company's keenness on the safety of its customers, and as a kind of support for the institutional sector and companies in light of the exceptional circumstances that the country is going through as a result of the economic repercussions of the precautionary measures taken to confront the risks of the spread of the new Corona virus.

Telecom Egypt announced a partnership with a submarine cable consortium that includes 7 international telecommunications service providers to establish the "2Africa" submarine cable, a huge cable that rotates around the African continent through 16 countries.

In addition to Telecom Egypt, the alliance includes China International Mobile Services Corporation, Facebook, MTN Global Connect, Orange, Saudi Telecom Company, Vodafone Group and Western Indian Ocean Cable Company.

Telecom Egypt's consolidated and independent financial statements for the first quarter of this year will be announced on Thursday, June 11.

Telecom Egypt (TE) said that the board has taken note of the appointment of Bakr Mohamed Abdel Wahab Mohamed El Bayoumi as a member of the company's board of directors.

The company said in a statement to the Egyptian Exchange today that Al-Bayoumi succeeds Tarek Mohamed Abdullah Al-Zaher.

The Egyptian Ministry of Public Business Sector (MPST) and Telecom Egypt (TE) have signed a cooperation protocol to implement the telecommunications infrastructure in the digital transformation project for the Ministry's subsidiaries, by providing telecommunications services using fiber optic technology.

According to a statement by the business sector today, Telecom Egypt will provide connectivity and internet services to these companies at high speeds through fiber optic cables, in order to enable and develop their digital transformation.

Telecom Egypt's board of directors has decided to appoint Mohamed Nasr El-Din as a member representing the government on the board of directors for the remaining term of the board, succeeding Hossam Shaaban Moussa.

The company said in a statement to the Egyptian Exchange on Thursday that it will be presented to the company's general assembly.

Telecom Egypt (ETEL) confirmed that it has not received any offers from the parties to the deal between Vodafone Group and Saudi Telecom Company, stressing that it has not been informed of the details of the discussions and terms of negotiations between the two parties.

Telecom Egypt said in a statement issued on Sunday that it is not in a position to comment on media news or statements published today, pointing out that any implicit reference to any role for Telecom Egypt in helping Vodafone International and Saudi Telecom to complete the deal is unclear and baseless.

Telecom Egypt (ETEL) confirmed that it has not received any offers from the parties to the deal between Vodafone Group and Saudi Telecom Company, stressing that it has not been informed of the details of the discussions and terms of negotiations between the two parties.

Telecom Egypt said in a statement issued on Sunday that it is not in a position to comment on media news or statements published today, pointing out that any implicit reference to any role for Telecom Egypt in helping Vodafone International and Saudi Telecom to complete the deal is unclear and baseless.

After more than 7 months, all scenarios are still available in the Vodafone Egypt deal after announcing the end of the memorandum of understanding with STC without reaching an agreement.

Last Sunday, STC announced the latest developments regarding the memorandum of understanding with Vodafone to acquire the group's stake in Vodafone Egypt, which includes the expiration of the memorandum of understanding without reaching an agreement to complete the transaction.

Telecom Egypt (TE) Managing Director and CEO Adel Hamed confirmed the continued implementation of infrastructure development plans across the country, ensuring the best level of services to customers.

This came on the sidelines of an inspection visit to a number of the company's work sites in Alexandria, to check on the progress of work and to find out the latest developments and modernization of the telecommunications network in the governorate, according to the Middle East News Agency.

Egyptian Prime Minister Mostafa Madbouly witnessed the signing ceremony of an agreement between the General Authority for Roads and Bridges and Telecom Egypt to settle the amounts due between them.

According to a statement issued by Egyptian ministers on Wednesday, the agreement comes in light of President Abdel Fattah al-Sisi's directives on the need to settle disputes and settle financial entanglements between government agencies and companies without resorting to litigation.

Telecom Egypt, Egypt's first integrated telecommunications operator and one of the largest submarine cable operators in the region, announced the expansion of its data center business with the construction of the largest international data center in Egypt.

The data center will be the first data center in Egypt to receive the Uptime Tier III certifications in the categories of design, facility construction and operational sustainability.

Telecom Egypt announced the date of announcing its financial statements for the first 9 months of this year.

The company said in a statement to the Egyptian Exchange on Monday that it will announce its consolidated and independent financial statements for the period ending last September, on Thursday, November 12, before the start of the trading session in both the Egyptian Exchange and London.

It is noteworthy that the company achieved profits of EGP 2.059 billion during the first six months of 2020, compared to profits of EGP 2.12 billion in the comparative period of 2019.

Telecom Egypt (TE) announced that the National Telecom Regulatory Authority (NTRA) has accepted and approved the company's financial and technical offer to obtain a 20 MHz bandwidth in the 2600 MHz frequency band using TDD technology under the usufruct system for a period of 10 years for USD 305 mn to be paid in 3 installments.  The company said in a statement issued on Thursday that it will pay 50 percent of the financial consideration in dollars upon signing, and 25 percent of the financial consideration in dollars, no later than a year from the date of signing, and 25 percent of the financial consideration.

The Minister of Communications and Information Technology Amr Talaat witnessed, via video conference, the signing of a strategic partnership contract between Telecom Egypt (TE) and AMS-IX to establish the Internet Traffic Exchange Center (EG-IX), located within Telecom Egypt's largest international data center in Smart Village, which holds Tier III – Uptime certification.

Telecom Egypt announced today its financial results for the financial period ended 30 September 2020, where net profit after tax reached EGP 3.5 billion, achieving a slight increase of 3%, compared to the same period of the previous year, due to the presence of several non-recurring factors in 2019. 

The company said in a statement issued today, that by neutralizing those effects, including the early retirement program, currency differences, the sale of Vodafone, one of its subsidiaries (VIS), and the impact of the decay of the first nine months of 2020

Telecom Egypt's 45% stake in Vodafone Egypt while providing a similar service is not a conflict of interest, said Minister of Communications and Information Technology Amr Talaat.  The minister added in an interview with the "Last Word" program yesterday, that with regard to the offer submitted by the Saudi Telecom Company to acquire Vodafone's global stake in Vodafone Egypt, the National Telecom Regulatory Authority is responsible for resolving this matter.

Mohamed Shamroukh, executive vice president of financial affairs at Telecom Egypt, said that the company succeeded in confronting the Corona virus as a result of investments in infrastructure development last year.  Shamroukh explained during the Egypt Economic Summit on Wednesday that the company continues to implement infrastructure development plans throughout the country, ensuring the provision of the best level of services to customers.

He added that the first phase of delivering digital transformation services to 5,000 government buildings has been completed so far.

Vodafone announced on Monday the end of its talks with the Saudi Telecom Company (STC) on the sale of Vodafone's 55% stake in Vodafone Egypt.

Vodafone Group CEO Nick Reed said it believes the Egyptian government is committed to an ideal framework for the telecommunications sector, which will enable Vodafone Egypt to achieve the country's vision of digitization and financial inclusion, and establish a technology hub to support its growth in the African region.

The Egyptian Minister of Communications and Information Technology Amr Talaat has witnessed the signing of new bandwidth allocation agreements.

Talaat said that the new frequencies will contribute significantly to improving telecommunications services, as they are subject to new quality standards, according to the Middle East News Agency.

Telecom Egypt's Board of Directors approved the 2021 budget and its operationally integrated companies

The company said in a statement to the EGX that the budget included total revenues ranging from single to medium to high, margin profit before interest, taxes, depreciation and amortization in the early thirties, and a capital expenditure rate of total activity revenues in the late twenties after excluding the cost of new frequencies.

Telecom Egypt (ETEL), Egypt's first integrated telecommunications operator and one of the largest submarine cable operators in the Middle East and Africa, has signed an agreement with Google.

The company explained in a statement issued today that under the agreement, transit services will be provided to Google's international traffic at the level of Internet protocols (IP Layer), which is the first of its kind in the field of transit services, through Telecom Egypt's international terrestrial network across Egyptian territory.

The Ministry of Social Solidarity and the Ministry of Communications and Information Technology (MCIT) in Egypt have signed a protocol to provide integrated telecommunications services to beneficiaries of social protection programs "Takaful and Karama Program".

According to a press release issued by the Ministry of Social Solidarity on Wednesday, the agreement comes within the framework of seeking to automate all services and the determination to strengthen the digital transformation system pursued by Digital Egypt, which aims to improve governance mechanisms for all data, in addition to improving the quality of services and ensuring a quick response to citizens' requests and complaints.

The Ministry of Social Solidarity signed a cooperation agreement with Telecom Egypt (WE) to provide free mobile phone services to beneficiaries of cash support programs from the poorest and neediest families and individuals.

In a statement issued today, the ministry explained that this comes with the aim of strengthening the principle of trust between the government and the citizen through receiving and responding directly to inquiries received and immediately addressing complaints and grievances received from citizens, as well as facilitating the coordination of tracking or verification procedures or other research studies.

Telecom Egypt announced its cooperation with IBM and Red Hat in developing telecommunications networks and accelerating the pace of digital transformation using an open-source hybrid cloud strategy. 

The company said in a statement issued on Tuesday that this cooperation comes within the framework of Telecom Egypt's strategy to achieve growth by developing and modernizing the infrastructure to provide computing services, infrastructure services and software services, which contributes to meeting the changing and accelerating requirements of its customers.

Telecom Egypt (TE) said that it will announce its consolidated and standalone financial statements for the period ending on December 31, 2020, in accordance with the Egyptian Accounting Standards, on Wednesday, February 24, before the start of the trading session on the Egyptian Exchange and the London Stock Exchange.

This came in a statement to the Egyptian Exchange on Monday.

According to the company's consolidated financial statements, its profits during the first nine months of last year amounted to about EGP 3.53 billion, compared to EGP 3.42 billion in the comparative period of 2019, taking into account minority rights.

Intercom Enterprises has won the tender of Telecom Egypt (WE) to design and implement an advanced customer service system, which includes all customer service centers nationwide that provide telecommunications services, whether landline, mobile or internet to WE customers. 

According to a statement issued on Thursday, the project aims to implement a new system to receive, follow up and resolve complaints as well as external requests for Telecom Egypt customers through customer service.

Telecom Egypt's Board of Directors has proposed distributing cash dividends to shareholders for 2020 profits.

The company said in a statement to the EGX on Wednesday that the proposal included distributing about EGP 8.53 billion to shareholders at a cash coupon of 50 piasters per share for last year's profits.

Telecom Egypt (ETEL), Egypt's first integrated telecom operator and one of the largest submarine cable operators in the Middle East and Africa, has announced its plan to launch the new submarine system HARP, which extends across the continent of Africa.

The company explained in a statement issued on Wednesday that this aims to connect its coastal and landlocked countries to Europe through Telecom Egypt's widespread land and marine infrastructure, and the system is scheduled to enter service during 2023.

Telecom Egypt's Board of Directors decided to convene the Ordinary General Assembly on Monday, March 29.

The company said in a statement to the Egyptian Exchange on Sunday that the general assembly will discuss the board of directors' report on the company's activities and financial statements for the past year, and approve the calculation of the proposed dividends.

The board of directors' proposal included distributing about EGP 8.53 billion to shareholders at a cash coupon of 50 piasters per share for last year's profits.

Telecom Egypt's Extraordinary General Assembly approved the amendment of Articles 21 and 43 of the company's Articles of Association.

The company said in a statement to the Egyptian Exchange today that the board of directors has been authorized to make any amendments that the General Authority for Investment or the Financial Supervisory Authority deems necessary to the resolutions of the assembly and the draft amendment.

Telecom Egypt recorded a consolidated profit of EGP 4.85 billion in 2020, compared to EGP 4.39 billion in 2019.

Telecom Egypt (TE) and the Suez Canal Authority (SCA), in coordination with the Signal Department of the Armed Forces, signed a contract to construct a new route for fiber optic cables for internet services between the Red Sea and the Mediterranean Sea via the Morshedin Road.

According to the contract, the three parties will cooperate to lay fiber optic cables through the guides road on the Suez Canal to connect Telecom Egypt's infrastructure networks, according to a statement issued by the Ministry of Communications on Thursday.

Telecom Egypt's Board of Directors decided to increase the dividend proposal for the year 2020 to become 75 piasters per share instead of 50 piasters.

The company said in a statement to the EGX that the decision came after Vodafone Egypt's ordinary general assembly approved the distribution of dividends worth two billion pounds, of which Telecom Egypt shares 900 mn pounds.

Adel Hamed, Managing Director and CEO of Telecom Egypt, explained that the company's proposed dividends are 3 times those of last year.

Telecom Egypt's Ordinary General Assembly approved the Board of Directors' report on the company's activities and financial statements for the past year 2020.

The company said in a statement issued on Monday that the general assembly approved the proposed dividend calculation for last year, where it was decided to distribute a cash coupon to shareholders at the rate of 75 piasters per share with a total value of EGP 1.28 billion.

Telecom Egypt (Telecom Egypt) has signed a cooperation protocol with Ora Developers to connect telecommunications networks and provide integrated telecommunications services in its real estate projects.

According to a Telecom Egypt statement issued today, the company will connect its networks and provide telecommunications services with the latest advanced technologies for real estate projects owned and affiliated with Ora Developers, through the technology of connecting fiber optic cables to residential units (FTTH), as well as providing integrated communications services within these projects.

The Egyptian Exchange (EGX) said that the right to distribute Telecom Egypt coupon will be transferred to the share buyer until the end of the session on Sunday, April 25, 2021.

The EGX added in a statement today that it has been decided to distribute coupon No. (19) at EGP 0.750 per share, as of April 28, 2021.

Telecom Egypt recorded a consolidated profit of EGP 4.85 billion in 2020, compared to EGP 4.39 billion in 2019.

Telecom Egypt (TE) and Sudatel Telecom Group (SUDATE) signed a Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) to enhance cooperation in the field of international connectivity between Egypt and Sudan. According to a statement issued on Wednesday, the protocol aims to achieve the optimal exploitation of the ground network linking the two countries and develop it with the latest technologies to support the transfer of international traffic, as well as linking the Sudatel landing station in Port Sudan and Telecom   The agreement was signed via video conference by Adel Hamed, Managing Director and CEO of Telecom Egypt, and Magdy Taha, CEO and General Manager of Sudatel Telecom Group. Egypt landing stations in the Red Sea and its submarine cables.

Telecom Egypt (Telecom Egypt) signed a cooperation protocol with Marakez Real Estate Investment Company, a subsidiary of Fawaz Alhokair Group, to provide internet service to the company's projects and provide integrated telecommunications services.

The company explained in a statement issued today that under the protocol, Telecom Egypt will connect its networks and provide telecommunications services to projects owned by Marakez Real Estate Investment Company, and provide integrated telecommunications services within these projects, including landline and high-speed internet services.

Telecom Egypt said it will announce its standalone and consolidated financial statements for the period ending on March 31, 2021, on Tuesday, May 11, 2021.

The company added in a statement to the Egyptian Exchange today that the financial statements will be announced before the start of the trading session in both the Egyptian Exchange and the London Stock Exchange.

Telecom Egypt recorded a consolidated profit of EGP 4.85 billion in 2020, compared to EGP 4.39 billion in 2019.

Telecom Egypt's consolidated financial statements for the first quarter of 2021 showed an increase in profits by 61.84 year-on-year.

The company said in a statement to the Egyptian Exchange today that its net profit reached EGP 2.12 billion during the three months ending in March 2021, compared to EGP 1.31 billion in the comparative quarter of 2020, taking into account minority rights.

The company's consolidated revenues rose to EGP 8.4 billion by the end of March 2021, compared to EGP 7 billion in the comparative quarter of 2020.

Telecom Egypt, Egypt's first integrated ICT operator, announced the launch of the "WE Access" service to support SMEs in developing their businesses and promoting digital transformation.  According to a statement issued by the company today, this comes by helping companies to link office and branch sites easily and with the highest levels of control and data security, in addition to providing data analysis services that greatly help support and develop marketing business.

The EGX decided to suspend trading on Telecom Egypt's shares. The bourse said in a statement today that the suspension is taking place until a statement from the company is announced.

The Minister of Communications and Information Technology Amr Talaat witnessed the signing of an amended shareholders' agreement between Telecom Egypt and Vodafone Group.

Egyptian Minister of Communications Amr Talaat revealed that 4 agreements have been signed between Telecom Egypt, Hatif Libya and Libyan International Telecommunications Company in the field of training and benefiting from technical and administrative expertise in various fields, in addition to a framework agreement for interconnection and making the Egyptian international cable network available to brothers in Libya.
Talaat said in a statement today that these agreements are the beginning of a serious, in-depth and multi-pronged phase of cooperation between Egypt and Libya in the field of communications and information technology.

Beltone Financial has set Telecom Egypt's fair value at EGP 16.20.  The company indicated in a research note issued on Thursday that it raised fair value following strong cash flows and audit expectations, and raised the recommendation to buy.

"We raised our fair value for Telecom Egypt to EGP 16.20 per share with the recommendation upgraded to buy following a potential rise of 22% from the current share price (+12% year-to-date)."

Telecom Egypt (TE) announced the scheduled date of announcing Telecom Egypt's financial results for the period ending on 30 June 2021.

The company said in a statement to the Egyptian Exchange today that the consolidated and standalone financial statements in accordance with the Egyptian accounting standards will be announced on Tuesday, August 10, 2021, before the start of the trading session on the Egyptian and London stock exchanges.

Telecom Egypt's financial indicators showed that its profits during the first half of 2021 increased by 87.8% year-on-year.

The company said in a statement to the Egyptian Exchange today that it achieved profits of EGP 3.87 billion during the first six months of 2021, compared to profits of EGP 2.06 billion in the comparative period of 2020.

The company's revenues during the period rose to EGP 17.37 billion, compared to EGP 14.94 billion in the comparative half of last year.

The 2Africa Alliance today announced the addition of four new 2Africa submarine cable landing sites that extend the cable's connectivity to Seychelles, Comoros and Angola, as well as a new landing site in southern Nigeria, joining the recently announced new Canary Islands landing site.

Telecom Egypt has signed a cooperation agreement with Amer Group to provide the latest integrated telecommunications solutions in its real estate projects.

Under the agreement, Telecom Egypt will connect its networks and provide telecommunications services with the latest advanced technologies for Amer Group's projects, by connecting fiber optic cables with FTTH technology for about 12k units, according to a statement issued on Thursday.

Telecom Egypt has issued a clarification regarding the publication titled "STC Saudi Arabia seeks financing to complete Vodafone Egypt deal".

The company said in a statement to the Egyptian Exchange today that it does not have any information regarding the news.

According to CNBC Arabia, banking sources said that the STC-Vodafone Egypt deal has resurfaced after it was disrupted last December after a year of negotiations for the Saudi company's acquisition of Vodafone's global stake in its Egyptian unit.

The 2Africa alliance, which includes China Mobile International, Facebook, MTN Global Connect, Orange of France, STC, Telecom Egypt, Vodafone International, African Telecommunications Company and IOC, today announced the expansion of cable connectivity by adding the new 2Africa PEARLS segment extending to the Arabian Gulf, India and Pakistan.
According to a statement issued on Tuesday, this extension will increase the total length of the 2Africa submarine cable system to more than 45,000 kilometers, the longest submarine cable.

Telecom Egypt (TE) has signed an agreement for a USD 500 mn medium-term syndicated loan to support capital expenditure and refinance existing short-term facilities.

FAB and Mashreq have been appointed as joint loan marketers, primary principal arrangers and underwriters, similar to the medium-term syndicated loan obtained in October 2018.

Telecom Egypt's Board of Directors has approved the company's estimated budget for the next year 2022.

The company said in a statement to the Egyptian Exchange on Thursday that the estimated budget included the growth of total revenues by a low bilateral percentage, with the decline in the volume of capital spending of the company.

She said that the decline in capital spending in light of the company's approach to completing the project to develop network capabilities and raise the quality of Internet services by replacing copper cables with fiber optic cables nationwide.

Telecom Egypt's net profit after tax increased during the first nine months of 2021 to EGP 6.1 billion compared to the same period of the year.

This came within the company's business results for the financial period ended 30 September 2021, according to the consolidated financial statements prepared in accordance with the Egyptian accounting standards.

Telecom Egypt's financial indicators showed that its profits during the first nine months of 2021 increased by 72.5% year-on-year.

The company said in a statement to the Egyptian Exchange on Thursday that it achieved profits of EGP 6.1 billion during the first nine months of 2021, compared to profits of EGP 3.53 billion in the comparative period of 2020.

Telecom Egypt's shares rose during today's session to the highest level since February 2019.

By 1:5pm today, Telecom Egypt was up 1.53% at EGP 15.3, a 34-month high.

Meanwhile, the value traded on the share reached EGP 61.21 mn through 4.02 mn shares.

The company's shares have risen 28.25% since the beginning of the year, trading EGP 3.28 billion through 254.7 million shares.

Beltone Holding's research unit expects more interest in EGX30 companies supported by profit-taking and the imposition of some adjustments to market rules in the second half of 2021.

According to Beltone's "Strategy 2022" report, most companies are expected to continue to grow to pre-pandemic levels, confirming the strong growth prospects for listed companies in the Egyptian market in 2022.

Telecom Egypt (Telecom Egypt), Egypt's first integrated ICT operator, has signed a cooperation agreement with the Chamber of Hotel Establishments to raise the efficiency of telecommunications infrastructure and provide integrated telecommunications services in hotels and tourist villages in Egypt.

According to a statement issued today, this comes within the framework of the cooperation protocol signed between the Ministry of Communications and Information Technology (MCIT), the Ministry of Tourism and Antiquities (MCIT), and the Signal Department of the Armed Forces. The agreement was signed by Telecom Egypt Managing Director and CEO Adel Hamed.

Telecom Egypt continued its current upward trend to climb near the May 2018 high.

At the close of today's session, the company's shares rose by 0.96% at EGP 16.91 per share.

The company's shares attracted EGP 19.95 mn in liquidity through 1.18 mn shares.

Telecom Egypt's Board of Directors decided to convene the Extraordinary General Assembly Meeting on Tuesday, February 22.

The company said in a statement to the Egyptian Exchange on Monday that the general assembly will discuss amending Article 22 of the company's articles of association regarding the formation of the board of directors.

Telecom Egypt posted a profit of EGP 6.1 billion during the first nine months of 2021, compared to EGP 3.53 billion in the comparable period of 2020.

The Egyptian Cabinet approved the renewal of the New Urban Communities Authority (NUCA) contract with Telecom Egypt to plan, implement, receive, operate and maintain terrestrial telephone networks in new urban cities.

According to a statement issued by the Council of Ministers on Wednesday, the renewal for a period of 3 years is renewable.

The Minister of Communications and Information Technology Amr Talaat and the Greek Minister of Digital Governance Kyriakos Piarakkis have witnessed the signing of a strategic Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) between Telecom Egypt (TE) and Grid Telecom, a subsidiary of the Greek Independent Electricity Transmission Operator (IPTO), to connect Egypt and Greece using submarine cable systems.

According to a statement by MCIT, Talaat visited Athens for one day to enhance joint cooperation between Egypt and Greece in the ICT field.

Telecom Egypt said that its consolidated and standalone financial statements for the fiscal year ending on December 31, 2021 will be announced on February 24, 2022.

The company said in a statement to the Egyptian Exchange (EGX) that the results will be announced in accordance with the Egyptian accounting standards before the start of the trading session on Thursday, February 24, in both the Egyptian Exchange and the London Stock Exchange.

Telecom Egypt has revised the date of announcing its consolidated and standalone financial statements for the financial year ending on 31 December 2021 to 3 March 2022, instead of the previously announced 24 February.

The company said in a statement to the Egyptian Exchange (EGX) that the results will be announced in accordance with the Egyptian accounting standards before the start of the trading session on Thursday, March 3, in both the Egyptian Exchange and the London Stock Exchange.

Telecom Egypt's Extraordinary General Assembly approved the amendment of articles of association.

The company said in a statement to the Egyptian Exchange today that the General Assembly approved the amendment of Article No. 21 of the company's articles of association, and authorized the board of directors to make any amendments deemed by the General Authority for Investment or the Financial Supervisory Authority on the resolutions of the assembly.

The Minister of Communications and Information Technology Amr Talaat signed an agreement between Telecom Egypt and Afrex Telecom, a telecommunications and infrastructure provider in Barcelona, on the landing of the Medusa submarine cable in Egypt, one of the largest submarine cable systems in the Mediterranean. The agreement was signed by Adel Hamed, Managing Director and CEO of Telecom Egypt, and Norman Alby, CEO of Afrix Telecom and Medusa, on the sidelines of the Mobile Phone International Exhibition and Conference held in Barcelona.

Telecom Egypt (TE) and Avery IX Telecom have signed a landing agreement for the Medusa submarine cable in Egypt.

According to a Telecom Egypt statement issued on Wednesday, the cable is one of the largest submarine cable systems in the Mediterranean, with a length of 8,760 kilometers.

The cable has 24 fiber pairs with a capacity of 20 terabytes per second per pair.

Telecom Egypt's board of directors has proposed a dividend of EGP 1 per share for 2021, with a growth rate of 33% compared to the previous year. 

Telecom Egypt achieved net profit after tax in 2021 of EGP 8.4 bln, a growth rate of 74% year-on-year.

Telecom Egypt (TE) said that the company's ordinary general assembly will discuss on March 28 the approval of the proposed dividend account for the year 2021.

The company added in a statement to the Egyptian Exchange today that the assembly will consider approving the appointment of board members for a new term.

The General Assembly discusses the adoption of the company's financial statements and the Board of Directors' report on the company's activities during 2021.

Telecom Egypt announced the completion of the full civil works for the submarine cable crossing route on the Suez Canal Road campus (Morshedin Road), which is one of the most important and shortest strategic axes for crossing international submarine cables from east to west.  According to today's statement, the length of the distance between the two landing points in Suez and Port Said is approximately 200 km, which is the lowest ground distance for crossing submarine cables at the international level.

Telecom Egypt (TE) has signed an agreement with the European Investment Bank (EIB), the European Union's financing arm, for a EUR 150 mn medium-term loan to expand its 4G broadband network.

The company said the move comes to develop and improve the coverage of its mobile network by creating 2,000 new locations for mobile towers and increasing the capacity of existing towers by adding new layers, according to the Middle East News Agency.

Telecom Egypt has decided to appoint Maged Ibrahim Osman as Chairman of the Board of Directors.   The company said in a statement to the EGX on Thursday that it was also decided to appoint Adel Hamed Ibrahim Gadallah as Managing Director of Telecom Egypt.

Telecom Egypt's right to cash distribution will close on Tuesday, April 19, the EGX said.

The EGX said in a statement issued on Monday that it was decided to distribute Telecom Egypt coupon No. (20) at EGP per share, as of April 26.

Telecom Egypt achieved net profit after tax in 2021 of EGP 8.4 bln, a growth rate of 74% year-on-year.

The company said in a statement to the Egyptian Exchange on Monday that it will announce the consolidated and independent financial statements for the period from January to the end of March on Tuesday, May 31.

Telecom Egypt announced the signing of a strategic memorandum of understanding with Etihad Etisalat Company "Mobily" to build the first direct dual submarine cable system linking the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia with the Arab Republic of Egypt.

The MoU includes discussing new and multiple options to connect international capacities west to Europe via Telecom Egypt network and east to the Arabian Gulf via Mobily's network, through the extension of the two companies' networks to connect them to a number of neighboring countries now and in the future.

Telecom Egypt's consolidated financial statements for the first quarter of 2022 revealed a decline in the company's profits by 35.8 year-on-year.

The company said in a statement to the Egyptian Exchange today that it recorded a net profit of EGP 1.36 billion during the period from January to the end of March, compared to EGP 2.12 billion profits in the comparative quarter of 2021, taking into account minority rights.

The share of shareholders' equity of the holding company in profits during the period amounted to about EGP 1.36 billion, compared to EGP 2.12 billion during the same period last year.

Telecom Egypt CEO Adel Hamed said the company is targeting a USD 1 billion operating profit this year. 

Hamed said in a press statement on the sidelines of a press conference on Thursday that Telecom Egypt is targeting revenues during 2022 worth $ 2.5 billion. 

The CEO pointed out that Telecom Egypt has invested about EGP 70 billion during the previous years.

Telecom Egypt and Etisalat Misr signed six strategic partnership agreements with investments of EGP 17 billion over the next 10 years.

Telecom Egypt (Telecom Egypt) and GRID Telecom, a subsidiary of the Greek Independent Electricity Transmission Operator (IPTO), announced the signing of a joint cooperation agreement to connect Egypt and Greece through the construction of a new submarine cable that follows one of the submarine cable systems extending across the Mediterranean Sea.
Telecom Egypt said it will announce its consolidated and standalone financial statements for the first half of this year on Thursday, August 11.

Telecom Egypt (TE) signed on Monday a commercial agreement with Orange Egypt to obtain local roaming services to ensure Telecom Egypt provides comprehensive and high-quality coverage of mobile services from voice and data, provided that the agreement extends for five years until the end of 2027.

Telecom Egypt's consolidated financial statements for the first half of this year showed that the company's profits declined marginally year-on-year.

The company said in a statement to the Egyptian Exchange on Thursday that it achieved a net profit of EGP 3.78 billion during the period from January to the end of June, compared to profits of EGP 3.87 billion in the comparative period of 2021, taking into account minority rights.

The company's revenues rose during the first six months of this year to EGP 20.4 billion.

Telecom Egypt and Orange Jordan announced the signing of a strategic cooperation agreement to establish a new international route linking Iraq with Europe through Egyptian and Jordanian territories.

The new route (CAB) CAIRO-AMMAN-BAGHDAD System is in line with the two companies' strategy to expand the provision of the latest high-quality telecommunications services to operators in the Middle East, specifically the Iraqi market, depending on the distinguished international infrastructure of the two companies through multiple submarine cables, according to the Middle East News Agency.

Telecom Egypt's shares rose in morning trading by more than 10% after denying receiving official purchase offers.

By 11:11 am today's session, the company's shares were up 10.48% at EGP 16.9 per share, trading EGP 17 mn across one million shares.

Telecom Egypt denied receiving any official offers to buy part of its stake in Vodafone Egypt.

Telecom Egypt (TE) announced that it has successfully completed the basic tests to operate eSIMs on its networks, in cooperation with major companies specialized in this field to provide the best technical solutions that ensure the provision of new advanced services.

Telecom Egypt CEO Adel Hamed said that the total investments to implement digital transformation projects within the first phase of a decent life amounted to EGP 8 billion, explaining that investments will reach EGP 11 billion by the end of the year.

Telecom Egypt, Egypt's first integrated ICT operator, has signed an agreement with the American company "LUMEN" to establish the first regional focal point for LUMEN in Egypt to provide internet services to telecommunications companies in Egypt, Africa, Asia and the Middle East, in partnership with Telecom Egypt and based on its distinguished international network.

Telecom Egypt (WE), Egypt's first integrated ICT operator, has signed a cooperation agreement with valU, the leading buy-now, pay later (BNPL) platform to promote the advanced lifestyle in the Middle East and North Africa, to provide product installments to customers at Wei branches.

Telecom Egypt confirmed that it has not received any official offer from any party regarding Qatar's USD 2.5 billion investment in Vodafone Egypt.

This came in a statement to the Egyptian Exchange in response to the publication entitled "Qatar's investment of $ 2.5 billion in Vodafone Egypt and other companies has reached an advanced stage."

Telecom Egypt announced the scheduled date for the disclosure of the results of the first nine months of this year.

The company said in a statement to the Egyptian Exchange on Sunday that it was decided to announce the consolidated and independent financial statements for the financial period ending on September 30, 2022, on Monday, November 14, 2022.

Telecom Egypt denied receiving official offers from any party regarding Telecom Egypt's stake in Vodafone Egypt. This came in a statement to the Egyptian Exchange on Wednesday in response to what is being circulated regarding the Qatar Sovereign Fund in the process of completing the acquisition of Telecom Egypt's stake in Vodafone Egypt.

The Financial Regulatory Authority (FRA) announced the filing of a draft optional tender offer submitted by Vodacom Group Limited (Vodacom) to purchase minority shares wishing to sell from Vodafone Egypt shareholders, in light of Telecom Egypt's intention not to respond to the purchase offer.  The Financial Supervisory Authority said in a statement on Sunday that accordingly, the offer of shares up to 124.608 shares at 0.05% of the capital shares of Vodafone Egypt Telecom at a cash price of 17.92 euros per share.

Telecom Egypt's consolidated financial statements for the first nine months of this year revealed that the company's net profit increased by 1.14% year-on-year. The company said in a statement to the Egyptian Exchange on Monday that it recorded a net profit of EGP 6.17 billion during the period from January to the end of September 2022, compared to EGP 6.1 billion during the same period last year, taking into account minority rights.

The company's revenues during the nine months rose to EGP 32.27 billion, compared to EGP 26.37 billion during the comparative period of 2021.

Telecom Egypt and Meta, members of the 2Africa submarine cable alliance, announced the success of the first submarine cable landing in Egypt in Ras Ghareb in the Red Sea Governorate, with another landing taking place in the Mediterranean city of Port Said at a later date.

Prime Minister Mostafa Madbouly witnessed, today, at the Government headquarters in the New Administrative Capital, the signing ceremony of a cooperation protocol between the Ministry of Justice and Telecom Egypt on providing real estate registration and documentation services through the company's headquarters, in the presence of the Minister of Justice Omar Marwan and the Minister of Communications and Information Technology Amr Talaat.

Telecom Egypt (Telecom Egypt) has signed an agreement with Greece's independent power transmission operator Grid Telecom to establish a maritime system linking Egypt and Greece across the Mediterranean.

The company said in a statement issued on Tuesday that the agreement aims to expand Telecom Egypt's international network and multiple access points to Europe by opening an eastern gateway to Europe through Greece.

Prime Minister Mostafa Madbouly has signed today a joint cooperation protocol between Telecom Egypt (Telecom Egypt) and the Egyptian Electricity Transmission Company (EETC) on finding a formula for joint technical cooperation between the two sides, within the framework of providing modern technical solutions that provide the required services in a secure manner, in the presence of the Minister of Electricity and Renewable Energy Mohamed Shaker El Markabi and the Minister of Communications and Information Technology Amr Talaat.

Telecom Egypt said in a statement that it will start providing services through nine branches at the present time, while working to expand the provision of services in other branches successively, as part of Telecom Egypt's efforts to provide added value to its customers, contribute to a development boom in digital transformation projects, and work to develop and improve the level of services provided to citizens in various sectors.

Telecom Egypt has revealed the fact that it has received USD 125 mn in new frequencies to serve its future expansions.
The company said in a statement to the Egyptian Exchange today that the new frequencies have not yet been signed and the matter is still under discussion with the National Telecom Regulatory Authority (NTRA), and the announcement will be made immediately after signing with the NTRA.

Telecom Egypt said it is considering a number of potential debt instruments to help finance its future expansions, including the issuance of future securitization bonds.  The company said in a statement issued on Sunday in response to what was published regarding its study of issuing futures rights bonds denominated in dollars, that the matter is still under study to choose the best appropriate financing methods and the timetable for their use.

Telecom Egypt (TE) announced that the National Telecom Regulatory Authority (NTRA) has accepted and approved its financial and technical offer to obtain a new 5 MHz bandwidth in the 1800 MHz frequency band using FDD technology with a 10-year usufruct system at a cost of USD 125 mn.

Telecom Egypt confirmed in a statement issued on Tuesday that the price is competitive compared to the frequencies obtained by the company in late 2020.

Telecom Egypt, the first integrated operator of ICT services in Egypt, announced that its International Data Center (RDH) has obtained the first Tier III operational sustainability gold certification in Africa from the American "Uptime" institute, which specializes in studying and evaluating global data centers, making Telecom Egypt the first and only company in Egypt and the African continent to obtain this certificate.

Telecom Egypt announced the date of disclosure of last year's financial statements.  The company said in a statement to the Egyptian Exchange on Tuesday that it will announce its consolidated and independent financial statements for the previous year on Monday, March 6.

Chairman of the Board of Directors of Azimut Egypt Investment said that there is not much information about the sale of part of Telecom Egypt at the moment.    In statements to the "Last Word" program on ONTV, Telecom Egypt is owned by the Ministry of Finance.

Telecom Egypt (TE) has issued an explanatory statement regarding the Egyptian government's intention to offer 10% of its 80% stake in the company's capital.

The company said in a statement issued on Tuesday that it had contacted the main shareholder, the Ministry of Finance, which stated that the matter was nothing more than a preliminary study that is still in the initial stages and stages.

She stressed that no formal decisions had been taken on this, which would conclude that it was futile to proceed with this proposal.

Telecom Egypt announced its cooperation with IBM to adopt the latest automation technologies and create a comprehensive solution for its Operations Support System (OSS) on mobile, landline and core networks, where Telecom Egypt will be able to modernize its IT system, reduce operating costs, and reduce the time required to monitor and solve technical problems in the network.

The Egyptian government has postponed the sale of a new stake in Telecom Egypt until global markets stabilize.  The government did not prefer to conduct an assessment under the pressure of market conditions, so the delay was to allow more time and stability in the markets, according to Sharq Economy with Bloomberg.

The global and Arab financial markets are witnessing a state of violent volatility due to fears of the repercussions of the global banking crisis.

Earlier this month, Egypt commissioned financial and legal advisers to explore the sale of an additional minority stake in the company already listed on the market and test investor appetite.

Telecom Egypt has decided to amend its dividend proposal for last year.  The company said in a statement on Sunday that it was decided to amend the proposal to become the value of the coupon 1.25 pounds instead of 75 piasters per share, subject to the approval of the company's general assembly.

Telecom Egypt's board of directors approved on Tuesday the appointment of Mohamed Nasr El-Din as managing director and chief executive officer, and Adel Hamed as a non-executive member of Telecom Egypt's board of directors.
Telecom Egypt's right to cash distribution will end at the close of Thursday, April 13, the EGX said.

Telecom Egypt's cash distribution right expires during Thursday's session.

Telecom Egypt coupon No. (21) will be distributed at EGP 1.250 per share, starting April 20, the bourse said in a statement today.

Telecom Egypt achieved a net profit after tax last year of EGP 9.2 bln, a growth of 9% compared to the previous year, supported by outstanding operational performance.

The Council of Ministers, during its meeting today chaired by Mostafa Madbouly, approved a contract with Telecom Egypt to implement the fourth phase to provide fiber optic infrastructure from the Digital Transformation and Digital Egypt project.

Telecom Egypt announced the success of the second landing of the 2Africa submarine cable system in Egypt, in Port Said on the Mediterranean coast.

This comes five months after the success of the first landing of the cable in the city of Ras Ghareb on the Red Sea coast, which was preceded by the completion of the delivery of the ground track of the cable inside Egypt in 2020 ahead of schedule, as well as the completion of the sea route linking the Ras Ghareb and Suez landing stations earlier last year.

Sources revealed to Bloomberg that the book-building for the sale of an additional 10% stake in Telecom Egypt is scheduled to close later on Thursday.  According to the agency, the price range for the share ranges from EGP 22.22 to EGP 27.16, while the number of shares offered is 170.7 mn shares.

CI Capital (CICH.CA), a leading diversified financial services group, announced today the completion of a EGP 3.75 bln secondary offering of Telecom Egypt (TE) with a total number of 162,171,802 shares, representing 9.5% of its issued capital.  The offering price was set at EGP 23.11 per share, which is the share price at the close of trading on Thursday 11 May, with a market value of EGP 39.5 bln for Telecom Egypt.

Telecom Egypt (Telecom Egypt) has announced the date of announcing its consolidated and standalone financial statements for the financial period ended 31 March 2023, prepared in accordance with the Egyptian Accounting Standards.

The Finance Ministry sells the second tranche of its stake in Telecom Egypt for EGP 196.2 mn.  The total value of the sale reached EGP 196.28 mn.

This transaction represents the second tranche within the Ministry of Finance's offering 10% of its stake in Telecom Egypt for sale, as it was decided to allocate the second tranche to the company's employees within the limits of 5% of the total offered shares, with a maximum of 8,535,358 shares.

The EGX announced the execution of a sale deal on Telecom Egypt shares during Monday's session.  The EGX said in a statement that today's session witnessed the sale of 41.75k shares with a total value of EGP 965.02k, as part of the segment allocated to employees.

The EGX announced on Sunday the sale of 8.49 mn shares of Telecom Egypt worth EGP 196.28 mn.
Telecom Egypt's consolidated financial statements for the first quarter of this year revealed that the company's profits increased by 180% year-on-year.

Mobile companies in Egypt are seeking to increase the prices of all services they provide by up to 30%. This comes as their profit margins have eroded due to high inflation and the decline in the local currency.

Egyptian Planning Minister Hala El-Said reviewed the details of the companies that the government succeeded in selling shares of to the private sector.  During a press conference held on Tuesday, Hala El-Said explained that a company that owns a number of hotels was offered to investors with the aim of increasing its capital with a minority share, and was awarded in the form of a capital increase of 37% to one of the alliances (Egyptian - foreign), with a total value of $ 700 million, which is a share of the capital increase.

Mubasher: Telecom Egypt (TE) announced the activation of the service on the Equiano submarine cable, the first submarine cable linking St. Helena Island to the world, representing a quantum leap in the efforts to promote the island's economic growth.

Telecom Egypt confirmed that it has not received any official offers regarding its stake in Vodafone Egypt.

Telecom Egypt announced the date of disclosure of the mid-term financial statements for the current year.
